We summarize each dive by two observables.
The $x$-axis is the total dive time $T$.
The $y$-axis is the maximum depth $D := max_(t) z(t)$, as shown in @fig:td-diagram.
The T–D plot uses an inverted $y$-axis: $D = 0$ is at the top, and larger depths appear lower.

